pan\" hclass=\"def\">in whatever way</span><ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">However you look at it, it's going to cost a lot.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">It's easy to reach the city centre, however you choose to travel.</span></li></ul>      </li></ol><span class=\"dictlink-g\"><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/american_english/however\" title=\" definition in American English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">however</span></a> in the Oxford Advanced American Dictionary</span><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/academic/however\" title=\" definition in Academic English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">however</span></a> in the Oxford Learner's Dictionary of Academic English</span></span><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/however\">however</a></div></div>\n","matches":[],"relatives":[],"nearBys":["Julia Ward Howe","Frankie Howerd","however adverb","howitzer noun","howl verb"]},[]]